) 
 

Send debiting information for one (free text) SMS for the given user to the UserModule or debiting information for one email for the given user to the UserModule.

Parameters:
user The user to debit.
inReq The Request to debit for, SearchRequest, RouteRequest and SMSSendRequest are supported.
ansCont The answer of the Request, may be NULL.
recipient The cellular number that the SMS was sent to or the email-address of the receiver.
message The message sent in the SMS or a short text describing the email, subject.
size The size of the message, number of SMS or size in bytes. If 0 then try to get it from other inparamters. Default 0.
Returns:
True if debited ok, false if not.

bool ParserDebitHandler::sendDebitInformation (  const UserItem *  user,
uint32  messageID,
uint32  debitAmount,
uint32  operationType,
char *  debitText,
uint32  size = 0,
const char *  extraUserOrigin = NULL
)  [private]
 

Send the debiting information to the UserModule.

This method is private, since it is only called by the "wrapper-methods" { make*Debit(..)}. If isCheckUser is set in the ParserThread then this method return true without doing anything.

Parameters:
user The user that have inserted the request into the server.
messageID A ID of this request that will be sent to the UserModule. This might be RequestID or RouteID.
operationType The type of operation that is performed, the types in DebitRequestPacket are supported.
debitText The text that will be inserted into the UserModule.
size The sise of the request that is sent to user (e.g. the number of SMS:es). Optional parameter with defaultvalue = 0.
extraUserOrigin If to use a extra string as origin text. E.g. phonenumber or IP-address.
Returns:
True if the debit information is registered in the module, false otherwise.
